  "text": "In Fig. 9 the geometry of a cod-end of square-mesh netting that is 109 meshes in length and 100 meshes in circumference is presented. The full mesh size (i.e. two bar lengths) of the netting is 100 mm, and the catch length in this example is 0.70 m. The calculated volume is 1.345 m 3 and the drag on the cod-end is 6340 N. A comparison is made with the model of Priour [CITATION_1] , and again the results are in very good agreement. Figure 10 shows the geometry of a rectangular-mesh cod-end. As in the last example, the cod-end is 124 meshes in length and 100 meshes in circumference. The mesh size is again 100 mm, but the mesh dimensions are such that the mesh bars in the direction of the cod-end length are 38 mm and those around the circumference are 72 mm. The catch length is again 0.70 m. Although the parameter values are similar to those of the square-mesh example in Fig. 9 , the dimensions of the rectangular mesh used here result in an overall cod-end geometry that is shorter and wider.",
